# Subagent Routing Mandate (Parent Agent)

The **parent agent** (main Composer session) orchestrates; **specialist subagents**
implement. Do not substitute "I'll do it faster inline" for the pipeline in
`.cursor/agents/` and `.cursor/rules/delivery-orchestration-constitution.mdc`.

## Mandatory first action (before edits)

Classify the user request, then **invoke `Task` immediately** when matched:

| Request class | First `subagent_type` | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Multi-step, full-stack, or ambiguous delivery | `delivery-orchestrator` | Single entry; orchestrator routes the rest |
| Backend behavior / Java / Flyway / runtime API | `backend-engineer` | After behavior spec if behavior-changing |
| Frontend behavior / Vue / Pinia / Playwright | `frontend-engineer` | Bank OA + i18n; E2E/UIUX gates follow |
| Behavior unclear or acceptance missing | `behavior-spec-author` | Blocks implementation until confirmed |
| Plan phase / COR-* / master-plan status | `plan-orchestrator` | Single active phase invariant |
| Requirements, PRD, matrix, API contract docs | `doc-keeper` | Before or with behavior code |
| Deep read-only audit (repo-wide, drift, review) | `explore` | Parallel OK; parent synthesizes |
| Docker deploy / compose / prod validation | `deploy-engineer` | After green gates |
| Task slice complete (behavior landed) | `post-task-doc-sync` | **Before** Done |
| After doc sync (when commit delegated) | `post-task-commit-review` | **Before** Done |

If multiple rows apply, start with **`delivery-orchestrator`** unless the user
named exactly one specialist.

## Parent agent MAY work inline (no Task) only when

1. **Read-only** answer — no file writes (explain code, compare options, status Q&A).
2. **Single mechanical edit** explicitly named by user (one typo, one line) with **no**
   behavior, API, permission, plan-status, or doc-source-of-truth change.
3. User **opts out in the same message** (e.g. "不要子 agent，只解释").

Everything else → **Task**, not inline implementation.

## Forbidden (parent agent)

- Implementing multi-file backend/frontend slices without `backend-engineer` /
  `frontend-engineer` (or orchestrator delegation).
- Updating `docs/plan/**` status, ledger, COR-* Done, permission matrix, or PRD
  without `doc-keeper` or `post-task-doc-sync`.
- Claiming **Done** without `post-task-doc-sync` (+ `post-task-commit-review` when
  commit is in scope per user/rules).
- Claiming frontend **Done** without `e2e-test-engineer` + `e2e-uiux-reviewer`.
- Large "deep review" via ad-hoc grep/read instead of `explore` subagent(s).
- Using `generalPurpose` when a named project specialist exists for the stage.

## Self-check (state in one line before first tool write)

`[routing] class=<…> → subagent=<…> → reason=<…>`

If `subagent=inline`, state the exception (read-only / single-line / user opt-out).

## Relation to other rules

- Pipeline order: `delivery-orchestration-constitution.mdc`
- TDD/BDD gates: `tdd-bdd-delivery-constitution.mdc`
- Doc sync / commit: `post-task-doc-sync-constitution.mdc`, `post-task-commit-review-constitution.mdc`

Agent definitions: `.cursor/agents/*.md` — read the target agent file before `Task`.
